  "text": "The encoded protein, a cadherin-related neuronal receptor, is involved in cell-cell connections in the brain. Cadherins have been shown to regulate neuronal migration, gray matter differentiation, neural circuit formation and synapse formation and remodeling. In addition several neuropsychiatric disorders, including autism and bipolar disorder have been associated with cadherin genes [CITATION_1] .",
